    "## Designing your Web Page (CSS)\n",
    "### To add custom style and format your HTML templates, you will need to create a Cascading Style Sheets (CSS). CSS is a style language considered static because there is no interaction with the code. \n",
    "\n",
    "#### In your <code><i>static</i></code> folder, create a file named <code><i>main.css</code></i>.\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "├── webpage\n",
    "│   ├── static\n",
    "│   │   ├── main.css\n",
    "│   ├── templates\n",
    "│   │   ├── feed.html\n",
    "│   │   ├── layout.html\n",
    "│   ├── main\n",
    "│   │   ├── __init__.py\n",
    "│   │   ├── routes.py\n",
    "│   ├── posts\n",
    "│   │   ├── __init__.py\n",
    "│   │   ├── routes.py\n",
    "│   ├── users\n",
    "│   │   ├── __init__.py\n",
    "│   │   ├── routes.py\n",
    "│   ├── __init__.py\n",
    "│   ├── models.py\n",
    "```\n",
    "#### CSS is a relatively straight forward language. \n",
    "#### This is the code I used to design the webpage shown in this blog. Feel free to adjust the CSS code in the <code><i>main.css</code></i> file to personalize the theme of your website to your liking.\n",
    "```\n",
    "body {\n",
    "  background: #E2C2B3;\n",
    "  color: #fff;\n",
    "  margin-top: 6rem;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {\n",
    "  color: #ffff;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    ".bg-steel {\n",
    "  background-color: #687477;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    ".site-header .navbar-nav .nav-link {\n",
    "  color: #E2C2B3;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    ".site-header .navbar-nav .nav-link.active {\n",
    "  font-weight: 100;\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    ".content-section {\n",
    "  padding: 4px 30px;\n",
